                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="16455700" author="apachespark" created="Fri, 27 Apr 2018 03:21:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;manbuyun&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/21175&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/21175&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16475205" author="joshrosen" created="Tue, 15 May 2018 02:29:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This bug was originally introduced in&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-21527&quot; title=&quot;Use buffer limit in order to take advantage of  JAVA NIO Util&amp;#39;s buffercache&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-21527&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-21527&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; so I think&#160;that this problem only impacts Spark 2.3.0+.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is a critical correctness issue and should be tagged as such, so I&apos;ve added the &lt;tt&gt;correctness&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;label and have promoted this to a BLOCKER.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16475274" author="apachespark" created="Tue, 15 May 2018 04:33:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;cloud-fan&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/21327&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/21327&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16475350" author="joshrosen" created="Tue, 15 May 2018 06:45:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;To work around this bug on unpatched / unhotfixed Spark 2.3.x releases, you can set the following Spark configuration at SparkContext creation time:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;spark.buffer.write.chunkSize 2147483647&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This effectively undoes the&#160;effects of&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-21527&quot; title=&quot;Use buffer limit in order to take advantage of  JAVA NIO Util&amp;#39;s buffercache&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-21527&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-21527&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
